- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method to estimate heterogeneous treatment effects using observational and experimental data, which involves machine learning techniques such as regression and classification. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses an application of the proposed method to improve Facebook page recommendations, which falls under the category of computational science and engineering. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper uses Facebook page recommendations as an example application, which involves social networks and information diffusion. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with the problem of identifying heterogeneous treatment effects, which involves designing and analyzing algorithms for data processing and statistical inference. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper uses observational time series data to estimate a mapping from covariates to unit-level effects, which is a common problem in information retrieval and recommendation systems.
